net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format

Class SegmentVariableLength

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format.Segment
      • net.sf.mmm.util.contenttype.base.format.SegmentVariableLength
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SegmentAny, SegmentKey, SegmentValue

    public abstract class SegmentVariableLength
extends Segment
    This class represents a Segment that can have a variable length.
    By default the length is unbound ([0, Long.MAX_VALUE]). If only the "length" attribute is specified in XML, then both getMinimumLength() and getMaximumLength() will return that value. If additionally the "maxLength" attribute is specified, then getMinimumLength() will return the value of "length" and getMaximumLength() will return the value of "maxLength".
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

      • getMaximumLength

        public long getMaximumLength()
        This method gets the maximum length of this Segment. Simple Segments like SegmentConstant have a fixed length. In this case the result of this method is the same as Segment.getMinimumLength(). Otherwise, the Segment is variable and this method returns a value greater than Segment.getMinimumLength(). Use Long.MAX_VALUE for an unbound segment like SegmentAny.
        Overrides:
        getMaximumLength in class Segment
        Returns:
        the maximum length.
